How do I set up the project locally? 
Install the dependencies ("npm i" in terminal), then run app.js in nodemon

What Node.js version is required? 
v22.13.0

How is the folder structure organized? 
\views\ contains all the ejs pages, along with the partials
\router\ contains the routers that calls for the requests in \controller\
\middleware\ contains middleware functions like authenticate
\public\ contains css and scripts that run client side
\model\ contain the schema for heroes
\controller\ contain get and post requests
\handler\ contain handlers for databases and the similar

How do I add new routes or CRUD operations? 
Write the request within a file in \controller\. Remember to connect it with a router and that back to app.js.

How are views rendered with EJS? 
EJS renders views with variables given by the get requests from \controller\

How do I handle errors and logging? 
Error middleware in Express, logging tools (e.g., Winston, Morgan).